pool.borrow()
├── when amount is zero
   └── it should revert (boundary)
├── given not active
   └── it should revert
├── given paused
   └── it should revert
├── given frozen
   └── it should revert
├── given borrowing not enabled
   └── it should revert
├── given price oracle sentinel is not zero and borrow is not allowed
   └── it should revert
├── when interest rate mode is not stable or variable
   └── it should revert
├── when borrowed amount surpasses the borrow cap
    └── it should revert (boundary)
├── when user is in isolation mode and asset is not borrowable in isolation mode
    └── it should revert
├── when user is in isolation mode and the isolation mode debt cieling is surpassed
    └── it should revert (boundary)
├── when the user's emode category doesn't match the borrow asset's emode category
    └── it should revert
├── when the user has no collateral
    └── it should revert
├── when the user has no LTV
    └── it should revert
├── when existing health factor is below 1
    └── it should revert
├── when resulting LTV is below the minimum LTV
    └── it should revert (boundary)
├── when user chooses stable borrow and it's not enabled (always for spark)
    └── it should revert
├── when user is using siloed borrowing and the asset doesn't match the silo
    └── it should revert
├── when user is NOT using siloed borrowing and the asset is siloed
    └── it should revert
├── when no time has passed since the last borrow
    ├── when it's the user's first borrow
        ├── when the user doing a regular borrow
            └── it should succeed
        ├── when the user doing a siloed borrow
            └── it should succeed
        ├── when the user doing an e-mode borrow
            └── it should succeed
        └──  when the user is borrowing in isolation mode
            └── it should succeed
    └──  when it's not the user's first borrow (same tree as above, updating isBorrowing)
        ├── when the user doing a regular borrow
            └── it should succeed
        ├── when the user doing a siloed borrow
            └── it should succeed
        ├── when the user doing an e-mode borrow
            └── it should succeed
        └──  when the user is borrowing in isolation mode
            └── it should succeed
├── when some time has passed since the last borrow (same tree as above, updating indexes)
    ├── when it's the user's first borrow
        ├── when the user doing a regular borrow
            └── it should succeed
        ├── when the user doing a siloed borrow
            └── it should succeed
        ├── when the user doing an e-mode borrow
            └── it should succeed
        └──  when the user is borrowing in isolation mode
            └── it should succeed
    └──  when it's not the user's first borrow (same tree as above, updating isBorrowing)
        ├── when the user doing a regular borrow
            └── it should succeed
        ├── when the user doing a siloed borrow
            └── it should succeed
        ├── when the user doing an e-mode borrow
            └── it should succeed
        └──  when the user is borrowing in isolation mode
            └── it should succeed
